WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.660
ChatGPT for PowerPoint changes
the way you build presentations.

00:00:03.680 --> 00:00:07.060
It turns scattered company context
into a streamlined workflow,

00:00:07.080 --> 00:00:10.400
helping you create an exec-ready,
customer-facing presentation

00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:13.280
in a fraction of the time.
When I open the ChatGPT window,

00:00:13.580 --> 00:00:16.880
I can start by organizing my thinking
before I build a single slide.

00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:21.160
I can bring in context from connected apps
like Google Drive, Microsoft 365,

00:00:21.540 --> 00:00:23.300
and internal communication channels.

00:00:23.580 --> 00:00:25.620
I can also upload files
from my local machine.

00:00:25.980 --> 00:00:30.000
In this case, I'm pulling together
messy meeting notes, account context,

00:00:30.020 --> 00:00:35.000
and other source material into one place.
Once I send that over, ChatGPT recommends

00:00:35.020 --> 00:00:39.360
a detailed structure for the deck.
It breaks the presentation down slide by

00:00:39.380 --> 00:00:44.720
slide, including suggested bullets,
tables, formatting, and overall flow.

00:00:45.180 --> 00:00:48.520
I can quickly review the outline,
make sure the direction is right,

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:53.320
and then ask ChatGPT to build the deck.
I can also give it additional guidance.

00:00:53.340 --> 00:00:57.520
In this case, I want to ensure it meets
the standards executives expect.

00:00:57.520 --> 00:01:01.220
So I'm going to use a skill called
Executive Readiness Quality Pass.

00:01:01.480 --> 00:01:05.780
This helps apply a quality bar,
formatting standards,

00:01:06.340 --> 00:01:08.940
and consistent communication
throughout my presentation.

00:01:09.320 --> 00:01:12.680
Now let's get to building.
ChatGPT creates the presentation,

00:01:12.840 --> 00:01:16.200
building it slide by slide.
It'll go through and apply the polish,

00:01:16.220 --> 00:01:19.280
and this is looking pretty good.
So the first version gives me

00:01:19.300 --> 00:01:22.340
a strong starting point.
But as I review it, I notice

00:01:22.520 --> 00:01:26.400
a few areas that I want to improve,
including some of the positioning language

00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:28.140
and meta commentary that made its way
into the deck.

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:31.220
So I can keep working with ChatGPT
right here in PowerPoint

00:01:31.400 --> 00:01:34.840
to refine the messaging
and tighten the final version.

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:39.160
You'll see those changes happen
right in line to the existing deck.

00:01:39.260 --> 00:01:40.900
Modifying the slide content.
Awesome.

00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:42.360
Very happy with the final result.

00:01:42.820 --> 00:01:46.920
ChatGPT for PowerPoint takes what used to
be a slow, manual process

00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:48.860
and turns it into a guided workflow

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:51.060
from raw inputs
to a high-quality deliverable.

